1962 JAGUAR E-TYPE XKE 3.8 LITER SERIES 1 COUPE. COPPER WITH TAN INTERIOR. CHROME WIRE WHEELS. GOOD DRIVING CAR JUST OUT OF STORAGE. NICE CAR FOR EASY IMPROVEMENT.

Offered for sale, from KURT TANNER MOTORCARS, is this pretty decent E-type two-seater coupe. This car was just purchased out of a Jaguar collection from it's long term owner in Iowa where I'm sure it didn't see much use recently. This car runs and drives OK but would benefit from a tune-up/service, tires, and simply being put to us by it's next enthusiastic driver. The car's cosmetics are older but seem OK currently for a decent driver.

The body on this car appears quite decent and straight. Gapping overall is decent and could use some fine tuning. It currently wears an older amateur paint job, OK as a driver, but upon closer inspection is showing plenty of cracking, lifting, poor prep work, and some skinning of filler in various places. The current copper color It would benefit greatly from a good repaint in it's original color, which appears to be factory Black, as seen deep up under the dashboard…
The car's underside appears fairly solid and decent, with only few repairs.

The interior trim is in fairly good condition, as it appears to be a specialist kit fitted in a correct Jaguar tan color. Seats are the updated 4.2 units which are more comfortable with the reclining ratchet system. The headliner could use re-gluing. There are a few loose ends that could use retidying on the interior trim, but it's in very nice condition overall, and certainly fine for a nice car.

The engine block currently fitted to the car is a later 3.8 E -type RA unit with a ZA prefix head. It's very clean and nicely detailed, suggesting evidence of a rebuild. The engine starts easily on the key, revs well, shows decent oil pressure with no smoke or noises. t's fitted with an electronic ignition. The car drives nicely down the road but would benefit from tires and a good thorough look over/ service. The clutch bites well, the gearbox shifts fine with a deliberate pause between gears ( like it should). The wire wheels fitted are in good shape and are the upgraded S2 units with the better forged hubs.
The car is complete except the fiberglass air cleaner box. A nice touch are the period Lucas headlights. The car still retains it's original data plate, matching body tag.
Production date is around mid-July, 1962.

Overall, a fairly good, running and driving 3.8 Liter Coupe for easy improvement. This car can be used and enjoyed right away. It would benefit from cosmetic improvements at some point in it's future. These early 3.8's are desirable for their purity of bloodline and raw race car character, and this pretty coupe is a smart investment going forward.

The looks of a classic English sports car with the performance of American muscle! This Jaguar XKE replica features a completely custom chassis built to fit the stunning curves of the E-type body. The Body on this XKE though is all fiberglass and lightweight. That paired with the massive 5.7L V8 under the hood makes for a truly unique driving experience! The Jaguar XKE has a special place in automotive history and has become the dream car for many car enthusiasts. The perks of having a replica of your dream car is you can make it your own without dramatically affecting the resale value. This one specifically is meant to be a great mix between performance and drivability. The 5.7L V8 punches out plenty of power and has limitless possibilities when looking to modify it while still providing reliability. The 700R4 automatic transmission allows the driver to focus on the curvy roads ahead while also providing an overdrive gear for easy freeway cruising. The ride is smooth and as you settle in to the bucket seats you will gain confidence with each corner. The lightweight and low center of gravity provides excellent cornering ability and the power is always there with a simple touch of the throttle. This is a great car for someone who is looking for something to take out on the weekends and tear up the back roads or turn heads and keep everyone guessing at the local cars and coffee event.
